<subSubSection id="62DD6540196429477486FEEFFE2FFD9A" pageId="52" pageNumber="627" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="2A7836CB196429477486FEEFFE8FFEA1" blockId="52.[212,1172,302,557]" box="[212,333,302,326]" pageId="52" pageNumber="627">
<heading id="713081A7196429477486FEEFFE8FFEA1" box="[212,333,302,326]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="52" pageNumber="627" reason="5">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD9196429477486FEEFFE8FFEA1" box="[212,333,302,326]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="627">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2A7836CB196429477486FE97FC6AFDCA" blockId="52.[212,1172,302,557]" pageId="52" pageNumber="627">
The specific epithet honours the ‘Xavante’, the name for an ethnic group of natives, used here as a noun in apposition. The Xavantes live in nine indigenous areas which are part of the territory they traditionally occupied for at least 180 years, in eastern 
<collectingRegion id="E803F829196429477486FE77FEB2FE2A" box="[212,368,437,461]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso" pageId="52" pageNumber="627">Mato Grosso</collectingRegion>
. The region where they live has suffered the environmental impact of extensive cattle ranching since the 1960s, an impact which is almost certainly irreversible. From the 1980s the impact has been intensified by the spread of giant grain farms, especially soybeans produced for export (
<bibRefCitation id="4E564B3A1964294776A9FDD4FC5AFDCA" author="Graham L" box="[763,920,533,557]" pageId="52" pageNumber="627" pagination="11" refId="ref29568" refString="Graham L. 2008. Xavante. Instituto Socioambiental, Povos Indigenas no Brasil [Internet]. [cited 2013 Apr 11]. Available from: http: // pib. socioambiental. org / en / povo / xavante / print /" type="journal article" year="2008">Graham 2008</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2A7836CB196429477486FDA4FE2FFD9A" blockId="52.[212,493,613,637]" box="[212,493,613,637]" pageId="52" pageNumber="627">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD9196429477486FDA4FE2FFD9A" bold="true" box="[212,493,613,637]" pageId="52" pageNumber="627">The sodalis species group</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="62DD6540196429477486FD02FE2DFBA6" pageId="52" pageNumber="627" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="2A7836CB196429477486FD02FE82FD3D" blockId="52.[212,1172,707,1089]" box="[212,320,707,730]" pageId="52" pageNumber="627">
<heading id="713081A7196429477486FD02FE82FD3D" box="[212,320,707,730]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="52" pageNumber="627" reason="5">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD9196429477486FD02FE82FD3D" box="[212,320,707,730]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="627">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2A7836CB196429477486FD2BFC94FC06" blockId="52.[212,1172,707,1089]" pageId="52" pageNumber="627">
The sodalis species group includes: 
<taxonomicName id="EDC74D48196429477638FD2AFD1FFCE5" authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1911" box="[618,733,747,770]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Megalopta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="627" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cuprea">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD9196429477638FD2AFD1FFCE5" box="[618,733,747,770]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="627">M. cuprea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="EDC74D481964294776BCFD2AFC56FCE5" authority="Santos &amp; Melo, 2014" authorityName="Santos &amp; Melo" authorityYear="2014" box="[750,916,746,770]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Megalopta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="627" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="munduruku" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD91964294776BCFD2AFC56FCE5" box="[750,916,746,770]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="627">M. munduruku</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="038057A21964294777CFFD2AFC19FCE5" box="[925,987,747,770]" pageId="52" pageNumber="627" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="EDC74D4819642947704AFD2AFB4EFCE5" box="[1048,1164,746,770]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Megalopta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="627" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sodalis">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD919642947704AFD2AFB4EFCE5" box="[1048,1164,746,770]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="627">M. sodalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Members of this species group can be recognized by having the mid portion of the basal area of the metapostnotum with depressed triangular area with longitudinal rugulosities branching from central rugulosities, or with transverse depression in 
<taxonomicName id="EDC74D48196429477020FC8AFE92FC65" authority="Santos &amp; Melo, 2014" authorityName="Santos &amp; Melo" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Megalopta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="627" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="munduruku" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD9196429477020FC8AFE92FC65" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="627">M. munduruku</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="038057A2196429477508FCAAFE59FC65" box="[346,411,875,898]" pageId="52" pageNumber="627" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, and by having the posterior upper margin of the metepisternum unmodified, lacking a velvety process in both sexes. Furthermore, this species group exhibits a large amount of intraspecific variation in the shape of the basal elevation of the labrum and in the basal area of the metapostnotum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2A7836CB1964294774ACFC2BFE2DFBA6" blockId="52.[212,1172,707,1089]" pageId="52" pageNumber="627">
<taxonomicName id="EDC74D481964294774ACFC2BFEB3FBE6" authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1911" box="[254,369,1002,1025]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Megalopta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="627" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cuprea">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD91964294774ACFC2BFEB3FBE6" box="[254,369,1002,1025]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="627">M. cuprea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in 
<collectingCountry id="52D0765B1964294775B5FC28FDF5FBE6" box="[487,567,1001,1025]" name="Bolivia" pageId="52" pageNumber="627">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
and northern 
<collectingCountry id="52D0765B19642947768EFC28FCDDFBE6" box="[732,799,1001,1025]" name="Brazil" pageId="52" pageNumber="627">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="B2FC2A4E196429477762FC28FC70FBE6" box="[816,946,1001,1025]" captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="53.[144,211,1560,1582]" captionTargetBox="[144,1104,168,1528]" captionTargetId="figure@53.[144,1104,168,1528]" captionTargetPageId="53" captionText="Figure 16. Distribution records of Megalopta species. (A) M. cuprea Friese; (B) M. munduruku sp. n; (C) M. sodalis Vachal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4004493" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4004493/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="627">Figure 16A</figureCitation>
), while 
<taxonomicName id="EDC74D4819642947705CFC2BFF3EFBC6" authority="Santos &amp; Melo, 2014" authorityName="Santos &amp; Melo" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Megalopta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="627" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="munduruku" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD919642947705CFC2BFF3EFBC6" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="627">M. munduruku</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="038057A2196429477555FBCBFE8AFBC6" box="[263,328,1034,1057]" pageId="52" pageNumber="627" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is found only in northern 
<collectingCountry id="52D0765B1964294776DBFBC8FD0EFBC6" box="[649,716,1033,1057]" name="Brazil" pageId="52" pageNumber="627">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="B2FC2A4E1964294776B2FBC8FCA0FBC6" box="[736,866,1033,1057]" captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="53.[144,211,1560,1582]" captionTargetBox="[144,1104,168,1528]" captionTargetId="figure@53.[144,1104,168,1528]" captionTargetPageId="53" captionText="Figure 16. Distribution records of Megalopta species. (A) M. cuprea Friese; (B) M. munduruku sp. n; (C) M. sodalis Vachal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4004493" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4004493/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="627">Figure 16B</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="EDC74D481964294777F9FBCBFBE0FBC6" box="[939,1058,1033,1057]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Megalopta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="627" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sodalis">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD91964294777F9FBCBFBE0FBC6" box="[939,1058,1033,1057]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="627">M. sodalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed (
<figureCitation id="B2FC2A4E19642947750CFBE8FE1DFBA6" box="[350,479,1065,1089]" captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="53.[144,211,1560,1582]" captionTargetBox="[144,1104,168,1528]" captionTargetId="figure@53.[144,1104,168,1528]" captionTargetPageId="53" captionText="Figure 16. Distribution records of Megalopta species. (A) M. cuprea Friese; (B) M. munduruku sp. n; (C) M. sodalis Vachal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4004493" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4004493/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="627">Figure 16C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
